Moin Aqeeb Ashraf (born 5 January 1992) is an English first-class cricketer, who played for Yorkshire County Cricket Club. His best season was in 2012 when he led Yorkshire's T20 attack with Mitchell Starc, helping Yorkshire reach the T20 finals day at Cardiff before losing to Hampshire in the final.He was released by Yorkshire, after five years at the club, in September 2015.
During the 2016 season he signed for Northants on a short term basis, to cover for injuries within the squad.
